docs.lead_paragraph: On the lower East Side is a tremendous market, featuring everything from soup greens to anchovies, including a well-stocked dairy counter. This store-within-a-store boasts, in addition to milk, butter and eggs, 190 varieties of cheese. A large number of these cheeses are imported; many are domestic, made in this country by adopted Americans and refugees who received their training on the other side.

headline.main: News of Food; Market Offers 190 Types of Cheese, Including Latin-American Varieties
